<font class="body">
<table width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0">
<tr align=left>
	<td colspan=2><font class="pressReleaseTitle">
		<b>TechTV Named Official In-House Broadcast Network of CES</b></font></td></tr>
<tr align=left>
	<td colspan=2><font class="pressReleaseSubTitle">
		<b></b></font><hr noshade size=1></td></tr>
<!--
<tr><td bgcolor="000000" colspan=2><hr noshade size=2></td></tr>
-->
<tr><td align=left><font class="pressReleaseLocation">
		<b>Arlington,VA</b></font></td>
	<td align=right><font class="pressReleaseDate">
		11/16/00</font></td></tr>
<tr><td colspan=2><hr noshade size=2></td></tr>
<!--
<tr><td bgcolor="000000" colspan=2><hr noshade size=1></td></tr>
-->
</table>

<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 width=80%>
<tr><td>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>
	<td><font class="pressReleaseBody">TechTV, the on-air and online network dedicated to the digital lifestyle and the Consumer Electronics Association (CEA) today announced that TechTV will be the official in-house broadcast network of the 2001 International Consumer Electronics Show (CES), the world's largest annual tradeshow for consumer technology, to be held January 6-9, 2001, in Las Vegas. <p>As the exclusive television network partner, TechTV will provide comprehensive, live coverage of CES.  The tradeshow attracts more than 110,000 attendees and over 1,700 exhibitors.  TechTV's coverage will include more than four shows a day, as well as the first annual "TechTV's Best of CES," an awards program recognizing and honoring the show's most outstanding, new consumer technology products.  <p>"TechTV is excited to partner with the CEA as the official network of the 2001 CES," said Joe Gillespie, executive vice president and COO, TechTV.  "CEA and TechTV share a common goal to highlight the best in consumer technology for digital consumers, and this partnership reflects that mission."<p>"This new collaboration allows for CES to come into 23 million homes through TechTV's nationwide TV programming and into any Internet-enabled home or business through TechTV's Web site," said Karen Chupka, vice president, conferences and events, Consumer Electronics Association (CEA), the sponsor, manager and producer of CES.  "As the official in-house broadcasting network, TechTV will help showcase CES as the worldwide source for workstyle and lifestyle technology, while at the same time highlighting its own editorial coverage of our industry, available everyday through its TV programming and Web site."<p>Through TechTV's multi-platform offering (TV, Internet and Web radio), consumers will have unlimited access to the show's breaking news, the hottest new products from the show floor and in-depth interviews with consumer technology personalities, innovators and decision makers.<p>"Since CES is not open to the public, TechTV provides the only opportunity for consumers to see the collection of amazing new electronic products prior to their launch into the marketplace," Gillespie continued.  "Anyone interested in augmenting their lifestyle with the coolest new digital and consumer electronic products will not want to miss TechTV's live television, radio and Internet coverage of CES." <br> <br>TechTV also will provide additional broadcasting services to CES attendees staying in local hotels, including daily events and schedules, CES transportation schedules and CEA association news.<p>About TechTV<br>TechTV, formerly known as ZDTV, is the on-air and online network dedicated to the digital lifestyle. Offering everything from industry news to product reviews, tech stocks to tech support, TechTV's original programming keeps the wired world informed and entertained. TechTV is one of the fastest growing cable networks, currently available in more than 20 million households and distributing content to 70 countries around the world.  With over 750,000 unique visitors per month, techtv.com is a community destination that encourages viewer interaction through e-mail, live chat and video mail.  TechTV is owned by Vulcan Ventures, Inc., which purchased it from ZD Inc., on January 21, 2000.<p>About CES and the CEA<br>The 2001 CES-Your Source for Workstyle and Lifestyle Technology will be held Saturday, January 6 through Tuesday, January 9 in Las Vegas, Nev.  For more news on CES before, during and after the show, visit www.CESweb.org, the interactive source for CES information.<p>CEA, a sector of the Electronic Industries Alliance (EIA), represents more than 600 U.S. companies involved in the development, manufacturing and distribution of audio, video, mobile electronics, communications, information technology, multimedia and accessory products, as well as related services, that are sold through consumer channels.  Combined, these companies account for more than $60 billion in annual sales.  CEA also sponsors and manages the International CES - Your Source for Workstyle and Lifestyle Technology.  All profits from CES are reinvested into industry services, including technical training and education, industry promotion, engineering standards development, market research and legislative advocacy.<p>###<p>Media Contacts: <br>Alyssa Donelan<br>Director of PR, TechTV<br>415-355-4427		<br>alyssa_donelan@techtvcorp.com<br>http://www.techtv.com<p>Amber McCasland<br>Porter Novelli for TechTV<br>415-733-1716<br>amccasland@porternovelli.com<p>Lisa Fasold<br>Director of Communications<br>CES<br>703 907 7669<br>lfasold@ce.org <br>http://www.CESweb.org
</font></td></tr>



</table>
